getDensity

public double getDensity(String kamName)
Returns the density of the KAM calculated as the number of KAM edges divided by the maximum number of edges possible between the KAM nodes: E / (N * (N - 1)) where N is the number of KAM nodes and E is the number of KAM edges. Zero is returned in the cases that the above expression is undefined.
